		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64568809"><p>Geothermal is only viable in the Big Island. There is a lot of solar, a little wind, and batteries, along with waste-to-energy incinerators-- but the bulk of energy is from oil.</p><p>More wind is a political challenge, but offshore wind will eventually be necessary. More solar is pretty easy, but distribution systems will need upgrades to make it work. There are a lot of ~40-story high-rises on Oahu, so a level of centralized generation is going to be necessary, but for the balance rooftop solar works well.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64568809">
