	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64569539"><p><div class="quote"><p>But the electricity has to come from somewhere.</p><p>Where does Hawaii get it?</p></div><p>As of three years ago 35% of its electricity was from renewables, the rest from oil. They do use geothermal on the island of Hawaii. They are on track to get to 70% renewable in 6 years (2030) and 100% by 2045. A 100% switch to renewables in Hawaii is slightly complicated by the fact that each island has its own grid so seven separate grids to build out to get to 100% (ignoring tiny N'iihau).</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64569539">

